org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl

Class AppParser

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.springframework.cloud.dataflow.core.dsl.AppParser
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    StreamParser, TaskParser

    public class AppParser
extends Object
    Parser for generating AppNodes from Tokens. This class may serve as a base for higher level app processing, for instance streams or tasks.
    Author:
    Andy Clement, Patrick Peralta, Mark Fisher

      • eatApp

        protected AppNode eatApp()
        Return a AppNode from the next token and advance the token position.

        Expected format: app: [label':']? identifier (appArguments)*

        Returns:
        an app node resulting from the next token

      • eatAppArgs

        protected ArgumentNode[] eatAppArgs()
        Return an array of ArgumentNode and advance the token position if the next token(s) contain arguments.

        Expected format: appArguments : DOUBLE_MINUS identifier(name) EQUALS identifier(value)

        Returns:
        array of arguments or null if the next token(s) do not contain arguments

      • eatArgValue

        protected String eatArgValue()
        Return the argument value from the next token and advance the token position.

        Expected format: argValue: identifier | literal_string

        Returns:
        argument value
